---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';

const path = '/guides';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'guides');
const desc = description(site, 'guides');

const guides = [
  {
    "slug": "tcpa",
    "title": "TCPA Compliance for Shopify SMS",
    "kicker": "TCPA & legal risk"
  },
  {
    "slug": "quiet-hours",
    "title": "Quiet Hours & Timezone SMS Sending",
    "kicker": "Quiet hours"
  },
  {
    "slug": "consent",
    "title": "SMS Consent Collection on Shopify",
    "kicker": "Consent architecture"
  },
  {
    "slug": "pricing",
    "title": "SMS Pricing & Cost-Per-Message Models",
    "kicker": "Message economics"
  },
  {
    "slug": "list-growth",
    "title": "SMS List Growth Without Consent Debt",
    "kicker": "List growth"
  },
  {
    "slug": "two-way-sms",
    "title": "Two-Way SMS & Reply Handling",
    "kicker": "Two-way SMS"
  },
  {
    "slug": "email-sms-coordination",
    "title": "Email + SMS Coordination Playbook",
    "kicker": "Channel coordination"
  },
  {
    "slug": "deliverability",
    "title": "SMS Deliverability & Carrier Filtering",
    "kicker": "Deliverability"
  },
  {
    "slug": "discount-discipline",
    "title": "SMS Discount Discipline",
    "kicker": "Discount discipline"
  },
  {
    "slug": "segmentation",
    "title": "SMS Segmentation on Shopify",
    "kicker": "Segmentation"
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="badge">Operator playbooks</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5">Shopify SMS guides — TCPA, consent, pricing, coordination</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">Deep playbooks for consent, quiet hours, message economics, two-way SMS, and email coordination. Sequenzy as lifecycle email layer beside Postscript and other SMS-native senders.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container pb-16 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {guides.map(g => (
      <a class="card" href={`/guides/${g.slug}`}>
        <p class="badge">{g.kicker}</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-black text-white">{g.title}</h2>
      </a>
    ))}
  </section>

    <div class="prose-shopify card mt-8">
      <h2>SMS operations depth 1: email-SMS collision rules for…</h2>
      <p>For <strong>guides index</strong>, email-SMS collision rules for cart recovery and product launches is not optional infrastructure. Shopify SMS apps that recover urgent revenue without wrecking consent treat every text as a scarce interrupt — cart recovery after meaningful checkout intent, launch access for opted-in VIPs, replenishment when SKU usage data supports timing.</p>
      <p>Postscript remains the SMS-native benchmark on this site: TCPA tooling, two-way replies, Shopify event triggers, and broadcast controls. Sequenzy is deliberately ranked as lifecycle email layer beside SMS — welcome depth, post-purchase education, winback arcs that should not be crammed into 160 characters. Klaviyo and Omnisend fit when one team wants bundled SMS with segmentation; Attentive when enterprise acquisition economics justify custom contracts.</p>
      <p>Run the math before scaling: platform fee plus carrier fee plus average discount per recovered order. A text that needs 25% off to convert may be negative contribution margin even when attribution dashboards look green. Pair channels deliberately — email for proof and education, SMS for timing — and never duplicate the same offer within twenty-four hours unless the subscriber opted into high-frequency updates.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Document opt-in source, message type promised, and maximum weekly frequency per segment.</li>
        <li>Configure quiet hours before enabling automations; audit checkout and popup copy quarterly.</li>
        <li>Assign one owner for reply inbox, suppression maps, and pre-launch TCPA review.</li>
        <li>Measure opt-out rate by flow, cost per incremental order, and full-price repeat purchase quality.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

